IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Narrative: On June 12, 2023, I, S/Tpr. Jeffrey Hoffmeister #6163 of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division Eastern Region received a case from Metropolitan Police Department of the District of Columbia [hereinafter referred to as MPD] regarding an extortion investigation. MPD met with the victim identified as Lincoln McCabe (12/28/2009) [hereinafter referred to as Lincoln]. While at a friends house located at 24880 Kelley Drive, Denton, MD 21629. Lincoln began communicating with an unknown subject [hereinafter referred to as the suspect] on the application Discord and Instagram. Lincoln used his webcam to speak with the suspect on Discord. Lincoln was enticed to masturbate by the suspect on camera, who later informed Lincoln he recorded Lincoln while he was masturbating. The suspect threatened Lincoln he would upload the video to YouTube and send the video to his friends and family just to ruin his life. Lincoln later informed his parents about this incident, and they drove to MPD to make a report. Based on the above, I have contacted the Lisa McCabe [hereinafter referred to as Lisa] the mother of Lincoln and obtained additional information. Lisa and MPD provided the Discord Username: callie_1905#1184 and Instagram Username: Calxlie_ andCelestia Haven as belonging to the suspect. I have sent subpoenas to Discord and Instagram to obtain information on the suspects accounts. Case open, investigation continuing.
